’Ł@2da9da856f6030a474290a5052f49b534c59c7b321d8edfe42afbea39f5ae522ŚīTitle: title: into string
Path: Examples
Content:
convert int to string and append three decimal places.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 5 | into string --decimals 3
5.000

```
convert float to string and round to nearest integer.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1.7 | into string --decimals 0
2

```
convert float to string.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1.7 | into string --decimals 1
1.7

```
convert float to string and limit to 2 decimals.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1.734 | into string --decimals 2
1.73

```
convert float to string.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 4.3 | into string
4.3

```
convert string to string.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '1234' | into string
1234

```
convert boolean to string.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> true | into string
true

```
convert date to string.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '2020-10-10 10:00:00 +02:00' | into datetime | into string
Sat Oct 10 10:00:00 2020

```
convert filepath to string.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> ls Cargo.toml | get name | into string


```
convert filesize to string.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1kB | into string
1.0 kB

```
convert duration to string.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 9day | into string
1wk 2day

```
convert cell-path to string.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> $.name | into string
$.name

```
